<title>UK: TABLE-TELEWEST H1 PRE-TAX LOSSES WIDEN.</title>
<headline>TABLE-TELEWEST H1 PRE-TAX LOSSES WIDEN.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>First half to June 30 1997</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		10.0 loss	    vs 8.3 loss</p>
<p> Pretax		     142.34 loss	  vs 117.51 loss</p>
<p> Turnover		   181.44		 vs 133.48</p>
<p>NOTE - As part of a business review, Telewest said it was slashing one quarter of its workforce as part of a strategic review and slowing the build-out of its network. The job cuts would lead to around 40 million pounds of cost savings in the first full year, it said. Earnings before tax, depreciation, interest and amortisation (EBITDA) rose to 16.37 million pounds from 7.07 million in the pervious half year, Telewest stated.</p>
<p>Full company name - Telewest Communications Plc.</p>
